@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 rounded-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white py-3">
            <h5 class="mb-0">
                <i class="bi bi-shield-lock me-2"></i>Privacy Policy
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body p-4">

            <p class="text-muted small">Last updated: March 2026</p>

            <h6 class="fw-semibold mt-3">1. Data Collection</h6>
            <p class="small">
                WMAS collects employee information including name, email, contact details,
                department, designation, attendance records, leave applications, and salary
                details solely for the purpose of workforce management within the organization.
            </p>

            <h6 class="fw-semibold mt-3">2. Data Usage</h6>
            <p class="small">
                Collected data is used exclusively for internal HR operations such as
                attendance tracking, leave management, payroll processing, and administrative
                reporting. Data is never shared with third parties.
            </p>

            <h6 class="fw-semibold mt-3">3. Access Control</h6>
            <p class="small">
                Role-based access control ensures that employees can only view their own
                personal records. Administrative access is restricted to authorized personnel
                only. All access is protected via ASP.NET Core Identity authentication.
            </p>

            <h6 class="fw-semibold mt-3">4. Data Security</h6>
            <p class="small">
                All passwords are encrypted using industry-standard hashing algorithms
                provided by ASP.NET Core Identity. Anti-forgery tokens are enforced on
                all forms. SQL injection is prevented through Entity Framework Core
                parameterized queries.
            </p>

            <h6 class="fw-semibold mt-3">5. Data Retention</h6>
            <p class="small">
                Employee records are retained for the duration of employment and may be
                archived as required by organizational policy. Users may contact the
                system administrator to request data correction or removal.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-4">
                <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Index"
                       class="btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm">
                    <i class="bi bi-arrow-left me-1"></i>Back to Dashboard
                </a>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</div>
